directions: Put ingredients into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in order given. Melt stick margarine in bottom of pan, then add remaining ingredients in order given previously.
Pour over top the Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Barely cover corned beef with hot water. Add onions and seasonings. Cover. Simmer about 1 hour per pound of meat or until tender. Remove meat from liquid. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover. Bring to boiling, Cook 10 minutes. Add cabbage. Cook 20 minutes more.

title: golden puffs
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Add last three ingredients.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar, flour, milk and eggs.
Use half of the batter and bake 2 layers.
Add to remaining batter the cloves, cinnamon and raisins.
Bake 2 more layers.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: vodka penne
directions: Saut garlic in oil for 1 minute, taking care not to burn the garlic. Add the vodka, then light it with a match. Watch that the vodka doesn't flame up too high and be very careful (very flammable). Add stock, cream, basil, tomatoes and the crushed red pepper. Let it get hot, then add the cooked noodles. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes as normal.
Add salt and pepper, stick of butter, sour cream and cream cheese.
Place in baking dish and cover with butter pats.
Top with sprinkled cheese.
Bake at 400° until butter and cheese melt, about 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's company's coming cake
directions: Mix, drain and set aside the cherries.
Set aside the brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sift together and set aside the flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Cream the butter, vanilla and sugar together.
Add the sour cream and beat until well blended.
Add the flour mixture to cream mixture alternately with eggs, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Beat well and scrape bowl frequently.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Top with 1/3 cherries and 1/3 nuts.
Repeat this a second and third time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: autumn squash-tomato casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter 5 minutes.
In buttered 2-quart casserole, layer squash and onions.
Measure seasonings into tomatoes, then pour over.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered at 375°, until crisp done, 40 minutes for tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white mountian frosting
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, and water for a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff and pour into syrup a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Spread on allready cooled cake.

title: curried fruit dessert
directions: Chop fruit.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and curry powder.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: Place torn lettuce in a large lettuce-leaf-lined bowl. Arrange apples around edge of bowl.
Arrange raisins, almonds, carrot and coconut in a circular design atop lettuce.
Cover and chill.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes lengthwise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place in saucepan with water and tight-fitting lid; steam until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Layer sweet potatoes in casserole.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beat.
Sift flour, cocoa, and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13x9x2-inch pan and bake 35 minutes at 300 degrees.
Take out, spread on marshmallows evenly, return to oven for 5 minutes.
Take out and apply frosting.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Puree sweet potatoes in food processor or blender.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg and potatoes.
Add dry ingredients with milk, nuts and raisins.
Do not overmix! Can sprinkle cinnamon and sugar to top.
Bake for 25 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes approximately 15 large muffins.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and place in frying pan over low heat.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon flour.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice onion rings and Polish sausage on top.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate kiss drops
directions: Beat until fluffy.
Add 2 cups self-rising flour; mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Wrap small amount of mixture around kisses. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool; dust with powdered sugar.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Is best if made a day ahead.

title: zesty party crunch(microwave)
directions: In a 4-quart microwavable bowl, microwave butter at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in cheese and seasoning. Add remaining ingredients, stirring well until all coated. Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Cool. Store in covered container.
Freezes up to 3 months.
Thaw at room temperature.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add brown sugar and eggs. Mix well with hands.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.

title: ten minute fruit cake
directions: Place egg whites in a small mixing bowl; beat until stiff. Set aside.
Combine mincemeat, raisins, walnuts, sugar, vanilla, melted butter and egg yolks in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Fold dry ingredients into mincemeat mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tangy fruit dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until thoroughly blended.
Serve with your favorite fruit or combination of fruits for a salad or dessert.
Makes 1 cup.

title: dad's broccoli and beef casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender; drain.
Fry beef until well done.
Rinse with hot water and drain again.
Add rice and seasonings.
Stir until mixed.
Put half of broccoli in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of beef and rice, cottage cheese, rest of beef and rice and rest of broccoli.
Spread soup over top and sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Pour enough beverage over sherbet to fill punch bowl and chill.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325°
for 45 minutes.
Can top with caramel sauce.
Serves 12.

title: "hot stuff" dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add pepper and tomato paste, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix.
Add cheese.
Keep in crock-pot.
(Use on crackers or chips.)

title: dill pickle - cream cheese swirls
directions: Bread should be ordered the day before you need.
Trim all hard edges and roll each slice flat as possible with rolling pin just before spreading with cheese mixture.
Place a dill pickle at end of bread slice and roll in a jellyroll fashion.
Wrap each roll in waxed paper separately and twist the ends so as to hold firm.
Chill overnight if possible.
When ready to serve, slice in approximately 1/2-inch slices.

title: e. c.'s zesty chilli
directions: Dump hamburger mixture into stew pot and continue to simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: sliced tomatoes with three herb dressing
directions: Place basil, parsley, oregano, olive oil, lemon juice, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper in a food processor fitted with the metal blade or a blender.
Process 30 to 60 seconds or until emulsified. Pour into a glass jar and set aside.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Boil diced potatoes and onion until tender.
With a potato masher, mash potatoes slightly.
Add mushroom soup, milk, oleo and cheese.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper and serve hot.

title: cold caramel sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; blend with egg.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add boiling water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in hot liquids; stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in orange sections and pineapple.
Whip cream and fold into mixture. Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold; garnish with a few green grapes that have been dipped in beaten egg whites and granulated sugar, to coat.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a large skillet; cook until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 1/2 hour or longer.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crunchy fish fillets
directions: Pat fillets dry.
Line bottom of baking dish with cereal, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dip fish into melted oleo and place in baking dish on top of cereal mix.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli with mustard-dill sauce
directions: Bring fresh broccoli and salted water to boil; cover and cook until just tender, about 6 minutes.
(Cook frozen broccoli as directed.)
Melt diet margarine; add flour and cook about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add salt, dill weed, mustard and milk.
Stir until smooth; bring to a simmer; cook 2 minutes while stirring constantly.

title: pineapple ice box pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk. Add cool whip and pineapple. Mix well. Pour into two graham cracker crust. Chill until it sets.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand. (Do not use mixer.) Makes 3 layers.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: Incredibly easy with spectacular results.
Makes a great family supper or bake at home and rewarm in the coals of a campfire.

title: cherry nut crunch(quick and easy and good)
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Pour in pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle broken nut meats over top. Top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with or without whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Then form into ball.
Roll cheese ball in nuts or press nuts on outside of cheese ball.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: In saucepan, cook beets in water until tender.
Drain.
Pour cold water over beets and skin them by rubbing between your hands. Cut off ends.
Slice beets.
Dissolve sugar and salt into the 2 cups water and vinegar.
Pour syrup onto beets.
These keep in the refrigerator for months.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Then in another bowl, mix 2 packages Dream Whip with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Mix pudding, Dream Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts together. Refrigerate.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet that has a tight-fitting cover.
Brown the pieces of chicken evenly on all sides in the melted butter.
Add the onions, green pepper, garlic, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Mix well, then stir in the wine, salt and pepper. Add the bay leaves and thyme.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 35 minutes.
Turn the chicken pieces once during this cooking period. They are done if you can pierce the thickest portions with a fork.
This chicken is excellent served with cooked spaghetti or cooked broad egg noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy cucumber dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl; stir until well blended. Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: lazy wife biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Spoon onto baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and butter until blended well. Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
Add granulated and brown sugars; mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in creamed mixture. Roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press and shape with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: quick honey dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly, then ready for use. Great with beef.

title: cherry punch
directions: Chill ingredients; mix well.
Add sherbet, stir.
Ice ring may be used instead of sherbet.
Serves about 20 people.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients to corn.
bake in 8 x 8-inch flat casserole placed in a pan of water at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage wheels
directions: Roll out pastries and spread uncooked sausage out to the edges.
Roll up as a log, chill and slice.
Bake on broiler pan at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: frogs' legs a la creole
directions: Put frogs' legs in boiling water with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Scald for 4 minutes.
Drain legs and pat dry.
Dip legs into eggs and roll in bread crumbs.

title: watergate pistachio cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or layer.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows; cook only until melted. Remove from heat.
Add coloring.
Add corn flakes; mix real good. Drop onto wax paper by spoonful; apply a few red hots to each. Allow to cool and serve.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: four minute fudge
directions: In sauce pan add sugar and cocoa. Add milk and stir. Bring to a boil. Boil for 4 minutes. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Add nuts. Drop by teaspoons full onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken or turkey into bite size pieces.
Wash mushrooms, pat dry and saute in butter with onion.
Follow package directions for firm rice.
Combine chicken, rice, mushrooms and onion.
Blend sour cream and undiluted mushroom soup.
Toss together with chicken mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.
Double the ingredients to serve 10 to 12.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, melted butter, lemon juice and coconut.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Pour melted butter into a baking dish.
Mix sugar, crushed pineapple (drained), bread, eggs and milk.
Pour over butter. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar, cinnamon and roasted pecans.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. (This is good served with ham.)

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and continue beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Fold in nuts and pour into 8 or 9 inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 300 degree oven
for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: *Can use Jell-O vanilla flavor sugar-free instant pudding and Cool Whip Lite whipped topping.

title: thyme roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
In a large bowl, stir together thyme, salt, garlic, and oil.
Add vegetables, and mix gently to coat.
Place vegetables in a 9x13 inch baking pan.
Cover with foil, and bake, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes. Uncover; continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring once until vegetables are tender and just start to brown.

title: ike's elk chile recipe
directions: Saute the mushrooms, onions, green pepper, garlic buds and celery and mix into the browned meat. Mix the tomato juice, tomatoes, pinto beans and kidney beans into meat mixture and add the cumin, chili powder, cayenne pepper, bay leaf and salt. Vary the seasonings to the taste you like. The above ingredients make a mild flavor. Simmer in large crock-pot for 6 hours or so.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Place whole graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and drizzle over graham crackers.
Put light cream cheese and Cool Whip into a bowl and blend well.
Spread one-half of this mixture over graham cracker crust.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture, the rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; mix egg and Parmesan cheese with spaghetti.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread with cottage cheese.
Cook meat and onion; drain and spread over cottage cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: karen's potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13 pan with non-stick spray.
Mix all ingredients right in pan.
Smooth top out.
Bake about 1 hour or until top is slightly browned. MARINATED VEGETABLES

title: norwegian te-brod
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, beaten eggs, extract and flour which has been sifted with baking powder, salt and cardamon.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in and spread with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes in 300° oven.
Remove and cool. Split lengthwise, then into slices.
Put on cookie sheet and put in 350° oven to brown.
Turn over and brown other side.

title: pear mincemeat(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Grind all fruit and mix with remaining ingredients.
Cook 2 hours slowly.

title: jane's famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, butter, sugar, brown sugar, real vanilla and eggs well. In separate bowl combine flour, soda and salt. Blend mixtures. Add chocolate chips. Drop big blobs of dough onto cookie sheet. Cook about 10 minutes. Cookies are done when they start to "tan".

title: hurry-up leftover rolls
directions: Spread 1/2 cup taco sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat 1 cup of taco sauce and add leftover meat and olives.
Place heaping tablespoon of meat mixture in center of tortillas and roll up tortilla.
Set in pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until thick.
Stir in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate and top with whipped cream.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients except broth in heavy frypan and cook until rice turns a slight transparent color or yellow, stirring constantly.
Place in a casserole dish with the broth.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream Shortening and Sugar until light.
Add Egg and Molasses; beat thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with Water; beating after each addition.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: sausage ring
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Lightly butter 9-inch ring mold.
Mix all ingredients and pack into mold.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Pour off excess fat and then cool 20 minutes more.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in skillet on low.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and chopped green onions.
Mix with meat sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin tin.
In a medium bowl, use a fork to stir in together corn meal, flour, both sugars, baking soda and salt.
In a small bowl, beat egg slightly with buttermilk and corn oil.
Join both mixtures and stir until moistened.
Spoon into prepared muffin tins.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan and cool before serving.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add strawberries and juice, crushed pineapple (drained), sliced bananas, nutmeats or coconut and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 15-inch cake pan or 2 small pans and freeze.
Take out about 10 minutes before serving.
Keeps well.

title: brownies
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, eggs, vanilla and corn syrup.
Mix ingredients for 2 minutes on low speed of mixer.
Scrape bowl and beaters during mixing.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 16 to 18 bars.

title: corn patch casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 2 quarts boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and pour into deep casserole.
Mix in corn, soup, milk, salt and Spam.
Top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: croissants
directions: Cream butter with 1/3 cup flour.
Chill and roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper into an oblong 12 x 6 inches.
Chill until ready to use.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak pickles in 2 gallons of water with lime for 24 hours. Next day, rinse 2 or 3 times and soak in clear water for 24 hours. Heat the remaining ingredients and pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, simmer for 45 minutes and seal.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cube roast; add meat tenderizer and Worcestershire sauce.
Let set 30 minutes.
Dice green onions and garlic.
Slice long strips of peppers.
Add remaining ingredients, then cook until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped pecans.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Parboil for 10 minutes the potatoes, green peppers and scallions.
Saute the beef until redness is gone.
Mix together cheese, salt, sugar and tomato sauce.
Place a layer of meat in a greased 2-quart casserole; cover with vegetables.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour tomato sauce mixture over all.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Steam broccoli; add other ingredients in microwave bowl and heat until all is melted.
Add cooked broccoli.
Use dip with king size Frito chips.

title: potato dumplings kartoffelkloesse
directions: Peel potatoes and cook in
boiling
salted
water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Let
stand several hours, uncovered, until dry.	Add flour, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Flour hands, form into 1 inch balls with crouton
in
center.
Drop
into a large kettle of gently boiling
salted
water.
Boil uncovered for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: clam balls
directions: Mix all together; form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter well.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each other.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Add and stir in extract.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Fritos.
Chill.
Just before serving, add Fritos and toss.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 375° to 400°. Cook 40 to 45 minutes with foil over the dish and 5 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat in soda and salt.
Stir in flour.
Shape in 1 inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press Hershey's Kiss in center of each ball.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown on bottom.
Cool slightly, then place on cooling racks.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: stuffed cheeseburgers
directions: Divide into 8 parts.
Flatten into very thin patties.
Season half of patties with salt and pepper and top with minced onion and cheese slice.
Cover with remaining patties and pinch edges together to seal.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve 1/4 cup chicken broth. Mix cracker crumbs and margarine over heat.
Put half in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients in bowl.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into small pieces.
Add to other ingredients in bowl, mix.
Pour into casserole and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour last half of cracker crumbs on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Brown in oven.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs.
Combine soda, flour and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add All-Bran and mix well.
Dates, currants, raisins or blueberries may be added, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This keeps well in the refrigerator 6 to 8 weeks.
Do not cover tightly.

title: snowy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash in large bowl with mixer.
Add softened cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light.
Blend in chives.
Spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, if desired.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar with a wire whisk.
Add the cabbage and carrots and mix well.
Let chill 1 hour.

title: hummers(frozen drink)
directions: Mix together and store in freezer.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: potatoes any way
directions: Choose one medium sized or large potato for each person at the table.
Wash and make sure all spots or imperfections are removed, but do not peel.
Dice potato into half inch pieces and place on baking sheet that has been liberally greased or sprayed with Pam.
A jellyroll pan makes a good baking pan.
Sprinkle potatoes with any good mixture of spices and/or herbs.
Spray with Pam.
I use powdered garlic, dried chives, powdered cheese like is used for Mac and cheese.
I often use curry or hot spices or sauces over the potatoes depending on how adventuresome the invited guests or family members are.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine egg, margarine, milk and lemon rind in bowl.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until combined.
Spoon batter into prepared 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs for 3 minutes; add 2 eggs and beat 3 minutes and add 2 more eggs, then beat 6 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add sugar and shortening to eggs. Then add sifted flour and baking powder; beat all for 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, using greased and floured tube pan.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage fine.
In a pan, add oil and fry onion until soft.
Add water, vinegar and apple; simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Add cloves the last 1/2 hour.
Taste for seasoning.
Blend with small amount of cornstarch or flour.
Serve with Rouladen and potato dumplings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Heat chicken, dice in sauce to which celery salt has been added.

title: pink delight salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in pineapple juice over low heat.
Mix jello in this mixture and cool.
Add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese and mix well.
Whip at high speed the Pet milk until stiff. Fold into mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: roast beef and sloppy joe mix
directions: Place roast in baking dish.
Place sliced bell pepper and onion on roast.
Place carrots and potatoes around roast.
Mix Sloppy Joe mix with tomato juice, then pour over roast.
Cover baking dish with foil, then put lid on baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until tender.

title: oscar's chili
directions: Cook beef; pour off fat.
Add sauce and beans.
Cook for 10 minutes over low heat, uncovered.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Pour lemon juice over peaches.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in milk, vanilla and salt.
In a large bowl, beat cream to soft stage.
Add milk mixture to cream and add 2 or 3 drops of food coloring.
Add peaches.

title: chicken parmesan(microwave)
directions: Place butter in flat casserole or pie plate.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Combine remaining ingredients, except chicken and paprika.
Dip chicken into melted butter and then into the crumbs.
Arrange in the casserole, thickest part toward the outside.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap or casserole cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Uncover and microwave another 5 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and sprinkle them into a pie pan sprayed with Pam.
Ingredients should be in bottom of pan.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and pour over ingredients in the pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Prick for doneness.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: crab patties
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well, shape crab mixture into 12 patties.
Pour oil into skillet (depth of 2 inches).
Fry patties until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, oil, eggs and crushed bananas; sift flour and all the spices.
Then add to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts last.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.
Use tube pan or loaf pan.
Let cool on a rack in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then dump.

title: corinne's cannon balls(appetizer)
directions: Crumble and fry sausage; drain well.
Combine sausage, Bisquick and cheese; mix well.
Form into walnut-size balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; blend the next 3 ingredients. Stir into tuna mixture.
Form into 4 patties.
Fry in lightly greased skillet over medium heat about 5 minutes or until browned. Serve on hamburger buns with lettuce and tomato slices.
Makes 4.

title: puffit
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk, then egg white, beaten stiff. Put in greased pan; bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in white sugar; press with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
These will melt in your mouth.

title: chicken soup
directions: To defat broth, place can in refrigerator overnight. Open and skim off fat.
In saucepan, combine all ingredients except pasta. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Stir in pasta. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.
(Low-fat.)

title: party mix
directions: Melt almond bark and oil on cookie sheet in oven.
Mix well other ingredients, spread thin on aluminum foil and break when cool.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini noodles as directed on package.
Chop all vegetables and cheese up while noodles cool in fridge at least 3 to 4 hours.
Rinse noodles and drain.
Add vegetables and dry seasonings.
Mix salad with spoons.
Pour at least 4 to 6 ounces dressing to taste over salad and mix again.
May need to add more seasonings and grated cheese to personal tastes.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: cloverleaf yeast rolls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Break yeast into small pieces and add warm water.
Mix all together and add melted (cooled) shortening.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Make dough into round ball and let sit in greased bowl for 10 minutes.
Work down and let raise double, about 1 hour.
Pinch off enough dough to make 3 balls that will fit into sections of a muffin pan.
Roll balls in melted grease.
Place 3 balls into each section of greased muffin pan.
Let raise double and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 cloverleaf rolls.

title: ooey gooey bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with electric mixer.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and vanilla with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut when cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry sausage with onions and garlic; drain well. Add cream cheese and stir until blended. Dip each mushroom into melted butter and stuff with mixture. Place in baking dish. Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt dorothy's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks (reserve egg whites) and mix.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately the flour mixture and the buttermilk.
Add lemon, orange and almond extracts.
Beat egg whites to peaks, then fold beaten egg whites into mixture.
Bake 1 1/3 hours at 350° in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture, then add chopped raw apples and chopped black walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven or until cake tests done.

title: taco dip
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Place in dish in order given. Serve with nacho chips.

title: cranberry spritzer
directions: Combine ingredients in a large pitcher, stirring well.
Serve over ice or well chilled.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread undrained pineapple in a glass 9 x 13 pan. Spoon in pie filling evenly over pineapple. Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer evenly. Spread butter slices on top. Sprinkle pecan pieces on top of butter. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm or cold.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add to corn along with sugar, nutmeg and salt. Pour into shallow baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in slow oven at 320° approximately 45 minutes.

title: fried sugar pies
directions: Place brown sugar and margarine in center of dough; crimp edges together.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
(Any thick preserves can be used in these pies, also.)
These are good for children's snacks or on coffee break.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and onion.
Add egg.
Gradually beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat in which fish was fried. Fry until golden brown.
Fat or oil should be deep and heated to about 375°.
Fry about 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper towels.

title: bacon cheeseburger pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink, drain and set aside. In the same skillet, cook bacon until crisp, remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels. Discard drippings. Drain pasta, add to the skillet. Add soup, beef and bacon, heat through. Sprinkle with cheese, cover and cook until the cheese is melted. Serve with barbecue sauce and mustard if desired.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Dilute soup with some of chicken broth.
Add diced chicken (use approximately 1 cup broth).
Mix together chicken mixture, chilies, cheese and tortilla chips.
Bake in 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° until bubbles form on top of cheese.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9 pan.
Smear margarine on bottom and sides of pan. Dip dry cake mix into bottom of pan mashing out the lumps as you go.
Cover cake mix with pineapple, then cover pineapple with blueberry pie filling.
Sprinkle and cover with brown sugar, then sprinkle chopped nuts over the sugar.
Slice the margarine thin and distribute over the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crush crackers and shred cheese.
Put a layer of crackers into the casserole dish.
Then add a layer of soup (a thin layer), then a layer of asparagus.
Do this until the casserole dish is full. The top layer must be crackers.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Then remove and place cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 10 more minutes. Cool and eat.

title: pizza hut pizza
directions: Dissolve in water the yeast and sugar. Add the remaining ingredients and knead. Let rise until doubled in size. Preheat oven to 475° with large black cast-iron pizza pan in oven. Put 2 tablespoons oil in pan. The pan gets very hot, so be careful. Divide dough into two. Roll out to fit pan and put into it. Top with pizza sauce, cheese and other toppings desired. Bake 8 minutes in 475° oven.
